2010-11-02

For JS_OPTIONS, use custom attributes instead of dummy elements.

http://dev.w3.org/html5/spec/Overview.html#embedding-custom-non-visible-data-with-the-data-attributes

The T_DATASET tag can be used to define the dataset for the element :

new WdElement
(
	WdElement::E_TEXT, array
	(
		WdElement::T_DATASET => array
		(
			'options' => array
			(
				'max-length' => 32,
				'min-length' => 4,
				'accept' => '[a-zA-Z]' 
			),
			
			'other' => 13
		)
	)
);

<input type="text" data-options="{ &quot;max-length&quot;: 32, &quot;min-length&quot;: 4, &quot;accept&quot;: &quot;[a-zA-z]&quot; }" data-other="13" />

The dataset is mirrored to the `dataset` property.

JSON encode arrays.




2010-08-01

Because HTML5 defines the ':required' speudo class, we should rename the WdElement::T_MANDATORY tag to
WdElement::T_REQUIRED.

http://dev.w3.org/html5/spec/links.html#selector-required

And maybe instead of the 'missing' class we should use the 'required' class on undefined required
elements, and the 'invalid' class on elements that didn't pass validation.

http://dev.w3.org/html5/spec/links.html#selector-invalid